title.narrative: OUTPUT 2: ACCES EDUCATION DE QUALITE

description.narrative: By 2016, 150,000 children, of which 80% are in the most remote targeted areas, have access to quality education based on an essential package which can be used as a standard for the definition of a national policy., which contributes to Equitable Access To Quality Education, Learning And Child-Friendly Schools, Learning Outcomes. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2016, girls and boys aged 0-14 years in the three poorest quintiles benefit from education policies to ensure equitable access to quality basic education and opportunities for early childhood development.
